## Tech Stack: React / TypeScript (Vite)

### Architecture
- Functional components with hooks
- Colocate related code (component + styles + tests)
- Use TypeScript strictly—no `any` types
- Prefer composition over inheritance

### React Conventions
- One component per file
- Named exports for components
- Use `useMemo`/`useCallback` only when needed (not by default)
- Prefer controlled components

### TypeScript Practices
- Define interfaces for all props
- Use type inference where obvious
- Avoid type assertions (`as`) unless necessary
- Generate API types from OpenAPI spec

### Styling
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Use CSS variables for theme values
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Dark mode support via Tailwind

### File Structure
```
src/
├── components/      # Reusable UI components
├── pages/           # Route-level components
├── adapters/        # API integration layer
├── utils/           # Pure utility functions
├── styles/          # Global styles
└── generated/       # Auto-generated types (don't edit)
```

### Prohibited
- `any` types
- Direct DOM manipulation
- Inline styles (use Tailwind)
- Console.log in committed code

